<F P=101> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soldiers Protest Budget Cuts Outside Defense Ministry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2301190194 Paris AFP in English 1953 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2301190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, Jan 22 (AFP) -- Belgian soldiers 
protesting about pensions and plans to trim the Armed Forces 
pelted police and the Defence Ministry building with eggs and 
tomatoes during a demonstration Saturday [22 January] in 
Brussels. 
  Around a thousand soldiers in civilian dress protested 
against the non-payment of pension increases and the plans to 
cut the Armed Forces. 
  While a delegation from the protesters met officials in the 
Defence Ministry, the crowd outside threw eggs and tomatoes at 
the building and police guarding it. 
  Several members of the delegation were hit as they came out 
of their meeting. 
  The crowd later dispersed without incident. 

</TEXT>

