<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pact for Italy To Form Alliance With Northern League </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401175294 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1615 
GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An agreement has been reached between Mario Segni's 
Pact for Italy and the Northern League. Segni, who was 
accompanied by [Rocco] Buttiglione, held a meeting this morning 
with Northern League Deputy [Roberto] Maroni. The meeting was 
described as positive and one which helped to resolve many 
differences. Segni said the meeting, which lasted four hours, 
was successful. A short time ago, a joint document was 
released. The document says, among other things, the Italian 
Republic is united and indivisible. This declaration was 
demanded by Segni, and it puts an end to the many secessionist 
statements made by the Northern League. 
  Now that the path has been smoothed over, the birth of a 
moderate alliance, which should also include [Silvio] Berlusconi 
and the Christian Democratic Center [Party], is set to go ahead. 
Observers are now waiting for a reaction from [Mino] 
Martinazzoli's Popular Party [new name of the Christian Democrat 
Party]. 

</TEXT>

