<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bonn Discovers, Halts Chemicals Bound for Iraq </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401154594 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1452 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The Federal Government today 
confirmed reports that chemicals, the export of which to Iraq 
would have violated the UN embargo against that country, have 
been discovered on board the German freighter "Asian Senator." 
Government spokesman Dieter Vogel announced in Bonn that the 
Federal Government received information in mid-December that two 
containers with ammonium perchlorate were being transported from 
China to Beirut. The freight was described as harmless material 
in the manifest, whereas in fact it was fuel ingredients for the 
Iraqi missile program. 

</TEXT>

