<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Navy To Send Ships To `Support' Somali Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2401195794 Mainz ZDF Television Network in German 1800 GMT 
24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2401195794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mainz ZDF Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Federal Navy intends to send ships to Somalia 
in mid-February to support the withdrawal of German blue helmet 
soldiers. According to information received by the Bonn studio 
of Second German Television, ZDF, this is intended to be a 
precautionary measure for the safety of the Bundeswehr units. 
It was said that the troops would board the ships in Mogadishu, 
while the equipment that was taken to Beledweyne will return to 
Germany on civilian freighters. 

</TEXT>

