<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Instead Party Considers Running for Bundestag </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501092894 Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG in German 24 Jan 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU2501092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "cob.": "Instead Party Goes Beyond Hamburg's </F>
Borders"] 
  [Text] Hamburg -- In Hamburg, the voters association Statt 
Partei [Instead Party] has decided in favor of nationwide 
expansion. Its participation in the forthcoming Bundestag 
election was not ruled out by Markus Wegner, the founder of the 
Instead Party, and other speakers. "We want our share in 
controlling the power in Bonn; we want to be there," Wegner 
said. Some candidates who were defeated in a vote announced 
that they would resign from the party. 

</TEXT>

