<H3> <TI>   Candidates Stress Moderation on Karelia Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2301201694 Helsinki Radio Finland in English 1930 GMT 23 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2301201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Radio Finland </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The presidential candidates, Elisabeth Rehn and 
Martti Ahtisaari, are both calling for moderate tones in 
discussions on the possible return of territory ceded to the 
Soviet Union at the end of the last war. At a joint appearance 
in the southeastern city of Lappeenranta, in the Finnish part of 
Karelia, Ms Rehn said that she has had numerous discussions on 
the issue with Russians. Mr. Ahtisaari said that time is needed 
before discussions with Russia on the possible return of the 
ceded parts of Karelia can begin. 

