<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis `Not Convinced' by Envoys </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2501092394 Nicosia I SIMERINI in Greek 25 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2501092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia I SIMERINI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by K. Venizelos] </F>
  [Excerpt] President Glavkos Kliridhis will not participate 
in talks on the so-called confidence-building measures nor in 
proximity talks on this package as proposed by UN Secretary 
General Butrus Butrus-Ghali. According to information received 
by I SIMERINI, President Kliridhis told the UN envoys Joe Clark, 
Gustave Feissel and John Paul Kavanagh, who presented him with a 
copy of the official reply letter of the Turkish Cypriot side, 
that, "this cannot be considered a positive answer on the 
package of confidence-building measures." 
  The same sources told I SIMERINI that the UN officials asked 
President Kliridhis to set aside the terms and conditions raised 
by Turkish Cypriot Leader Rauf Denktas so that talks may begin 
immediately. "Consider that the terms have not been set and 
that a the issue of the confidence-building measures will be 
resolved during the talks," the UN envoys insisted. But the 
president was not convinced. Things will certainly be clarified 
today when the UN secretary general's envoys again meet with 
President Kliridhis and Denktas. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

