<H3> <TI>   Former National Bank Boss Dies; 17 November Declaration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2401224594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 2203 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2401224594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Former National Bank Director Mikhail 
Vranopoulos died at 2125 [1925 GMT] at Evangelismos Hospital. 
Doctors announced that following surgery, there were 
complications, and violent hemorrhaging caused his death. 
[passage omitted] 
  In a declaration to the private television station SKY, the 
terrorist group 17 November claimed responsibility for the 
attack on the former National Bank director. The declaration 
said that Vranopoulos and the former New Democracy government 
were responsible for the scandalous sale of the public cement 
company Ayet Iraklis. The declaration added that many people 
believed 17 November had dissolved because it had not attacked 
for some 13 months. Police are investigating the declaration. 
  According to other information, 17 November said the police 
have wrongly accused it of attacks it did not perform. 

</TEXT>

