<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ciller, Yilmaz Meet With Israeli President Weizman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2401204494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2401204494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Turhan Ipek video report] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Israeli President Ever 
Weizman received Prime Minister Tansu Ciller at his hotel and 
conferred with her for some time. During the meeting, which 
lasted approximately 45 minutes, Weizman extended to Ciller a 
letter from Israeli Prime Minister Rabin inviting the Turkish 
prime minister to visit Israel. Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin 
also attended the meeting. 
  In a statement to TRT in connection with the meeting, 
Ambassador Volkan Vural, chief adviser at the Prime Minister's 
Office, said that Ciller informed the visiting president that 
Turkey supports the Middle East peace process and wishes to 
contribute to it. Vural noted that within this framework, 
Ciller touched upon the development of regional economic 
cooperation and the introduction of new institutions in the 
region. Vural added: 
  [Begin recording] The prime minister underlined that new 
institutions are needed in the Middle East. She suggested that 
these institutions could encompass the development of economic 
cooperation among regional countries, the creation of joint 
projects, and the introduction of new structures that would meet 
the regional security needs of all the countries in this area. 
[end recording] 
  According to Vural, Israel's water demands from Turkey were 
also discussed during the meeting. Agreement was also reached 
to expand cooperation in the struggle against terrorism. 
  Weizman then received Motherland Party [ANAP] leader Mesut 
Yilmaz. In a statement after the meeting, Yilmaz reported that 
he told Weizman that, as the main opposition party, ANAP will 
support future moves to develop relations with Israel. Pointing 
out that there is still a significant distance to be covered in 
bilateral relations, Yilmaz expressed the hope that there will 
be an acceleration in the development of relations in light of 
the new political developments. 
  President Suleyman Demirel will host a dinner in Weizman's 
honor at the Cankaya Mansion this evening. 

</TEXT>

