<H3> <TI>   Weizman Asks al-Asad To Make `Bold Decision' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2501054194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 25 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2501054194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israel's President Ezer Weizman, on an official 
visit to Turkey, has issued a call to Syrian President Hafiz 
al-Asad to make a courageous decision about meeting Israeli 
leaders face to face for peace. At a dinner in honor in Ankara, 
Weizman also sent condolences to al-Asad on the death of his son. 
  [Begin Weizman recording, broadcast in progress] ....to send 
my condolences to President al-Asad for the loss of his son. I 
hope that he will continue to lead his country on the road to 
peace. I believe that President al-Asad, when he says Syria 
made a strategic decision for peace, I believe in his sincerity 
and integrity. He is a man of honor, but he has to understand 
that in peace, like in war, one has to recognize the mentality 
of one's counterpart. It seems to me that in Geneva, he failed 
to understand the expectations of public opinion in Israel. I 
do hope that in the near future he will make a bold decision and 
meet Israelis, meet the prime minister, meet the foreign 
minister, talk to them, understand them, and know the spirit of 
the country. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

