<H3> <TI>   Klestil Not To Resign Over `Private Matter' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501110694 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 25 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2501110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "t.c": "I Will Go Through This Difficult </F>
Period"] 
  [Text] Vienna -- Indifferent to the media war that has 
erupted over his person and the crisis in his marriage, 
President Klestil stated that he is optimistic and full of 
energy. "I will go through this difficult period," he stressed. 
Thus, the president will give a speech at a ceremony of the 
pope's UN representative in Vienna on the occasion of World 
Peace Day under the slogan "Year of the Family." "I will 
naturally underline the value of the family, but I will also 
point out that I have seen in my personal life recently how 
these values can be endangered easily," Klestil told DIE PRESSE 
yesterday. 
  The main speech at the ceremony, organized by Nuncio 
Squicciarini, will be delivered by State Secretary Cardinal 
Sodano from the Vatican. In the interview with DIE PRESSE, 
Klestil left no doubt that he does not have any intention of 
resigning because of this private matter. 

