<H3> <TI>   Antiterrorist Police Arrest 10 Alleged PKK Supporters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501121894 Paris AFP in English 1156 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2501121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Marseilles, France, Jan 25 (AFP) -- Ten alleged 
supporters of the Kurdish Workers Party (PKK) were arrested here 
on Tuesday [25 January] on suspicion of extorting funds for the 
separatist organisation, which is banned in Turkey. 
  Police, including officers from an antiterrorist unit, 
carried out the sweep following the arrest of the presumed head 
of the network on Monday. 
  Police, who searched the homes of the ten, said the PKK 
contributions were "not always voluntary, violence was often 
used to get the money." 

</TEXT>

