<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Romanian Deputies Request Lifting of FRY Embargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501200294 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2501200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dan Preda report from Strasbourg] </F>
  [Excerpts] Currently the plenary session of the 
Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe is debating the 
situation in former Yugoslavia, more precisely, the effects of 
the embargo instated against former Yugoslavia [by the UN 
Security Council] on the economy of the neighboring countries. 
The afternoon session began with the speech of Thorvald 
Stoltenberg. [passage omitted] 
  The floor was also taken by Dumitru Buzatu, Romanian Chamber 
of Deputies member [and Vaslui deputy on behalf of the Social 
Democracy Party of Romania], who pointed out that, currently, 
further losses are registered in Romania's economy, which so far 
amount to over $7 billion. Senator Adrian Paunescu also took 
the floor to discuss that issue. He asserted that the embargo 
should be lifted and the principle of dialogue should be 
introduced. Romania is suffering, the PSM [Socialist Party of 
Labor] senator said, merely because of the wish to make Serbia 
suffer. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

