Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Talks With 'Arafat To Prepare EU </F>
Support for Gaza and Jericho"; as released by Brussels TEXTLINE 
database] 
  [Text] The Vice President of the European Commission, Mr. 
Manuel Marin, met PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat in Tunis on 
Thursday afternoon [13 January]. The two mainly discussed the 
conditions of application of Community aid to the organization 
and, in particular, the appropriation of ECU500 million decided 
by member states immediately after the signing of the Treaty of 
Washington in September between Israel and the PLO. Mr. 'Arafat 
has announced that an estimated budget will be brought to the 
Community's knowledge and that of other donors in order to 
enable them to determine the cost of installation of the 
Palestinian authorities in the occupied territories and in the 
first phase in Gaza and Jericho. Mr. Marin recalled the 
priorities laid down by member states in the use of Community 
aid, especially toward social sectors: education, health and 
training. A Palestinian delegation of experts will be in 
Brussels, probably in February, for more in-depth talks on this 
matter. 

