<F P=102>  BR2501110994 London HERMES Database in English 20 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2501110994 </F>
<F P=104>  London HERMES Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [UK press release from the Ministry of Defense: "Contract </F>
for New FRS 2 Sea Harriers Confirmed"] 
  [Text] 20 Jan -- A contract for 18 new FRS2 Harrier 
Aircraft was confirmed today by Jonathan Aitken, Minister for 
Defence Procurement. Answering a parliamentary question from 
Keith Mans MP, Mr Aitken said: 
  "In order to sustain the Royal Navy's sea Harrier force well 
into the future, I am pleased to announce the decision to 
purchase a total of 18 new FRS2 aircraft and to convert a 
further 5 FRS1s to FRS2s under the current Mid Life Update 
programme. Contracts for the programme are being placed as 
satisfactory terms are agreed, under the Department's `No 
acceptable price, no contract' -- NAPNOC procedures, in order to 
secure best value for money. The contract for the 18 new 
aircraft has now been placed with British Aerospace at a value 
of some 200 million pounds." 

</TEXT>

