<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Official Urges Attention to Afghanistan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401153594 Hamburg DPA in German 1452 GMT 14 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1401153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Helmut Schaefer, the minister of state 
at the Foreign Ministry, has expressed clear criticism of arms 
exports from Islamic countries to Afghanistan. He explicitly 
mentioned Saudi Arabia, Iran, and Pakistan. Everything has to 
be done to halt the flow of weapons. 
  Schaefer expressed concern about the civil war that has 
flared up again in Afghanistan. The situation has led to floods 
of panic-stricken refugees moving to Pakistan. The minister of 
state estimated the number of refugees at more than 250,000. He 
called upon the Bundestag to take up the question of the 
Afghanistan conflict. 

