<H3> <TI>   Police Accuse Political Editor of Spying for GDR </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201114894 Hamburg DPA in German 1017 GMT 22 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2201114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Karlsruhe (DPA)--The investigating magistrate of the 
Federal Court of Justice (BGH) has issued a custody order for 
Gerhard Fleischle, 55, the chief political editor of 
Deutschlandfunk radio (Cologne). The Federal Prosecutor's 
Office said today that the journalist is accused of having 
worked for the GDR Ministry for State Security's Intelligence 
Department since 1960. The man had been provisionally detained 
on Thursday [20 January]. 
  According to the investigation so far, the editor primarily 
supplied information about his colleagues and about journalistic 
projects to his employers in East Berlin until 1989. He is also 
assumed to have passed on information about the EC and NATO when 
he was a correspondent in Brussels between 1979 and 1984. 

</TEXT>

