Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed HC; SH: "Breaking Windows at Iranian Embassy </F>
in Bern; Mujahideen Deny Being Implicated"; as released by Bern 
ATSA/SDAA database] 
  [Text] Bern, 25 Jan (ATSA) -- The mojahidin of the people 
of Iran have rejected any implication in the attack on the 
Iranian Embassy in Bern on Monday [24 January]. In a 
communique, the Bureau of the Mojahidin in Paris denies the 
"story fabricated" by IRNA, the official Iranian press agency. 
The spokesperson at the Public Ministry of the Confederation 
said the Iranian Embassy in Bern has three months to file a 
complaint. 
  Municipal police arrested two Iranian nationals on Monday 
for 
throwing stones at and breaking four windows of the [embassy] 
building. They were released early in the evening. According to 
the mojahidin, the Iranian regime hopes to impede the 
extradition of the murderers of Professor Kazem Radjavi by tying 
this action to their movement. 

