<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Approves 1994 Economic Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601105094 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1016 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2601105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The German Cabinet today approved 
the 1994 annual economic report submitted by Economic Affairs 
Minister Guenter Rexrodt. A spokesman for Rexrodt said the 
cabinet also approved a draft for the abolition of the Rebates 
Law. 
  According to the annual economic report, the German 
Government is expecting a further increase in the number of 
unemployed by around 450,000 to nearly four million. Economic 
growth should amount to 1-1.5 percent with the rate of inflation 
running at around 3 percent. Rexrodt is to give a news 
conference (at 1300 GMT) to discuss details of the report. 

</TEXT>

