<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mitterrand Gives `Warning' About Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501181094 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2501181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Francois Mitterrand, who visited Nantes today, 
said he is concerned about unemployment and the decrease in 
social security benefits. [passage omitted] 
  In a speech at the Town Hall, President Mitterrand called 
for 
national unity and solidarity to protect the weakest citizens 
against the strong, and he gave a warning to the international 
community about Bosnia: 
  [Begin Mitterrand recording] We need an international law to 
settle all this. (?We will see) Sarajevos everywhere if the law 
of might is the international rule, if the United Nations is not 
able to make its voice heard, if the civilized nations are not 
in a condition to establish peace and reconciliation. What an 
immense retreat that will be after we had all shouted together: 
Long live freedom! Those who waited for it for half a century, 
three quarters of a century, who suffered in concentration 
camps, those who saw their nearest ones, their parents, their 
brothers, their children, die in pain and under torture, will 
turn away from freedom, and will stop believing in it. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

