<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian Embassy Denies Bakhtiar Assassination Allegations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501142894 Tehran IRNA in English 1353 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2501142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris, Jan. 25, IRNA -- The Iranian Embassy here on 
Tuesday [25 January] categorically denied Iran's involvement in 
the 1971 assassination in Paris of Shapur Bakhtiar, the last 
prime minister in the former regime of Iran. 
  In a statement released here the Iranian Embassy also 
condemned any act of terrorism. The statement was a response to 
allegations recently raised by French papers that Iran had been 
involved in Bakhtiar's assassination. It underlined the need 
for the French judicial system to maintain its independence and 
keep aloof from any hue and cry while investigating the case. 
  The AGENCE FRANCE PRESSE in a news dispatch on Monday 
accused 
Iran of providing logistical assistance in the assassination of 
Bakhtiar. The Iranian Embassy advised that no prejudgement 
should be made on the issue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

