<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Progressive' Forces Unite on Government Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501223294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1906 GMT 
25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2501223294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Delegations from the PDS [Democratic Party of the 
Left], the AD [Democratic Alliance] and the Christian Socials 
have met and decided to unite on a common program for government 
to be presented to the other progressive forces. 
  The points of convergence indicated in a communique issued 
at 
the end of the meeting were: the continuation of economic and 
financial reconstruction started by the [Prime Minister Carlo 
Azeglio] Ciampi government and radical innovations in social 
policy. 
  The progressive round table will meet again next week 
immediately after the PSI's [Italian Socialist Party] general 
assembly. 

</TEXT>

