<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Arms Imports To Offset International Debt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501152694 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Swedish 
1300 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2501152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swedish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia's debt to Finland, which runs into the 
billions, will be partly reduced by Finland buying weapons from 
Russia. This involves weapons and ammunition worth 450 million 
Finnish Marks granted in a supplementary budget last year. 
Finland is to receive portable anti-aircraft missiles, among 
other things. The deliveries will be specified in a couple of 
weeks, the Defense Ministry says. The total Russian debt to 
Finland is just over 6 billion Finnish Marks. 

</TEXT>

