<H3> <TI>   NATO, Romanian Officials Discuss Partnership for Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701120794 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1031 GMT 27 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2701120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels ROMPRES, 27/1/1994 -- After an interview 
with NATO Deputy General-Secretary Amedeo de Franchis on 26 
January, Romanian Foreign Minister Teodor Melescanu stated to a 
ROMPRES correspondent that a general exchange of opinions was 
made on the occasion regarding "security in southeast Europe, 
the prospects opened by the Partnership for Peace (PFP), as well 
as its contribution brought to stability in the mentioned area 
and to Romania's stability." 
  "We also approached the issue regarding the concurrent 
support that we wish to gain from the alliance for the 
elaboration of the necessary documents regarding our offer of 
participation in the Partnership for Peace and I may say that 
the answer was extremely positive and determined," Melescanu 
said. 
  The Romanian top diplomat also added that consultations were 
already held regarding "technicalities and administrative 
issues" related to the future appointment (under the 
Partnership's provisions) of liaison active officers with the 
alliance headquarters and with "the gray cell" of the 
Partnership for Peace headquartered at Mons. 

</TEXT>

