<F P=103> BR2501090194 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels EUROPE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Lithuania Seeks To Negotiate </F>
Association Agreement"; as released by Brussels TEXTLINE 
database] 
  [Text] Mr. Januska, Lithuania's minister of foreign 
affairs, has sent a letter to Mr. Carolos Papoulias, Greek 
foreign minister and president of the Council of the [European] 
Union, requesting that the Council authorize the European 
Commission to negotiate an association agreement with Lithuania 
as soon as possible. "The support of the presidency of the 
European Union" to this effect "would be of great importance for 
the future prosperity of Lithuania, as well as for the stability 
and security of the whole Baltic region," the letter states. It 
will be recalled that the Twelve found the negotiating 
directives proposed by the European Commission for the Baltic 
states to be too limited and have expressed the intention of 
going further in creating closer ties with these countries. 

