<H3> <TI>   Commissioner Comments on Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2101151794 Brussels RAPID Database in French 21 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2101151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels RAPID Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [EC Document No. DOC/IP/94/43: "Nuclear Security and </F>
Efficiency in East Europe"; as released by Brussels RAPID 
database] 
  [Text] Commission Vice President Henning Christophersen 
welcomed the adoption by the European Parliament yesterday of a 
project which will contribute to financing the improvement of 
the safety and efficiency of nuclear sites in the countries of 
Central and East Europe as well as in the Republics of the 
former USSR. 
  The Commission proposal will allow a total of ECU1.1 billion 
in EURATOM loans to be earmarked for this project. 
  The vice president stressed that the text adopted by the 
(European) Parliament confirms that the Parliament as well as 
the Commission deem improving nuclear safety a priority. 
According to Mr. Christophersen, a political consensus has 
already been reached within the Council. Quick approval of the 
decision, which will make the program operational, is expected, 
and the efforts already made within the framework of the PHARE 
[Economic Reconstruction Aid for Poland and Hungary] and TACIS 
[CIS Technical Assistance] programs thus will be enhanced. 
  The proposal is in line with the conclusions of the European 
Council of Lisbon in June 1992. 
  The decision will be implemented in cooperation with the 
European Bank for Investment, which will assess the projects in 
economic and financial terms. 
  According to the vice president, this decision will make it 
possible for the Commission to initiate an important program in 
line with its priorities in the field of security, environmental 
protection, and foreign relations. 

</TEXT>

