<F P=102>  LD2501112994 Hamburg DPA in German 1051 GMT 25 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2501112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Munich (DPA) -- Roman Herzog, president of the 
Federal Constitutional Court, will run for election 23 May as 
federal president. In a fax message to Christian Social Union 
[CSU] Chairman Theo Waigel, Herzog said today that he is 
prepared "to run for election and to assume the office of 
federal president if successful." CSU General Secretary Erwin 
Huber stated this at the Munich press club. Leading members of 
the Christian Democratic Union and the CSU nominated Herzog as 
their joint candidate to succeed Richard von Weizsaecker 
yesterday evening. 

