<H3> <TI>   Poison Packets Found on North Sea Islands </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501121694 Hamburg DPA in German 1534 GMT 25 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2501121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Norderney/Oldenburg (DPA) -- Packets containing the 
highly poisonous pesticide Apron Plus have been found for the 
first time on the North Sea islands of Norderney and Juist this 
afternoon. The Weser-Ems District Council in Oldenburg confirmed 
that two packets had been clearly identified. The contents of 
three other packets still had to be tested. 
  Authorities estimate that around 130,000 packets of Apron 
Plus had been collected on the Dutch coast by yesterday evening. 
About 70,000 more packets are drifting eastward off the Dutch 
North Sea islands. They come from the French freighter the 
Sherbro. It lost 88 containers last December. 

</TEXT>

