<H3> <TI>   Herzog Officially Accepts Candidacy for Presidency </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2601132294 Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG in German 26 Jan 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU2601132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "ker/hh": "Roman Herzog Accepts Candidacy"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Karlsruhe/Munich -- The president of the Federal 
Constitutional Court, Roman Herzog, officially declared his 
willingness to run for the office of federal president. 
According to the court, he sent identical letters to Christian 
Democratic Union [CDU] Chairman Helmut Kohl and Christian Social 
Union [CSU] Chairman Theo Waigel, informing them that he wants 
to run for president. Herzog had said for weeks he would not 
make his final decision until the CDU/CSU leadership had 
nominated him officially. On Monday evening [24 January], the 
CDU and CSU leaderships agreed to ask the 59-year-old Bavarian 
to run for president, to be elected by the Federal Assembly in 
Berlin on 23 May. Until then, Herzog wants to remain a 
constitutional judge and president of the court. [passage 
omitted]. 

</TEXT>

