<H3> <TI>   Former IBM Officer Sentenced to 12 Years for Treason </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701105294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0835 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (ADN-BLN) -- The Second Criminal Bench of 
Berlin Higher Regional Court today sentenced a 61-year-old 
former IBM security officer from Wilhelmshaven to 12 years 
imprisonment for treason. 
  Between 1975 and 1980, the defendant passed on some 35,000 
sheets of confidential military documents from an archive of the 
IBM Special Systems company [IBM Sondersysteme] to the main 
Department II of the MfS [former GDR Ministry for State 
Security], which handled counterintelligence. In the event of a 
military conflict, the betrayal could have led to the complete 
destruction of NATO's navy. 

</TEXT>

