<H3> <TI>   GDR Funds To Benefit New Laender, Berlin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2601132494 Duesseldorf HANDELSBLATT in German 26 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2601132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Duesseldorf HANDELSBLATT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "agr": "DM400 Million to Eastern Laender"] </F>
  [Text] Berlin -- For the first time, the new laender and 
Berlin will get millions from the property of parties and 
organizations of the former GDR for community purposes. The 
Independent Commission for the Examination of the Property of 
GDR Parties and Mass Organizations has now released 400 million 
German marks; 60 percent of the money is to benefit economic 
restructuring and 40 percent is for social and cultural 
purposes. The Federal Government wanted to provide the funds 
for current expenses, but the Commission insisted on their 
exclusive use for investment or promotion of investment. A 
legal dispute over the money, particularly with the Party of 
Democratic Socialism [PDS], cannot be ruled out. Therefore, the 
Federal Government is guaranteeing the funds provided to the 
laender, it was stated. 

</TEXT>

