<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Announces Entry Into Political `Fray' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601173894 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 1700 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Uno Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Silvio Berlusconi has announced his candidacy on 
air. He has just announced his entry into politics. He will 
stand for Forza Italia at the forthcoming elections because, he 
said, he no longer wants to live in a country governed by 
immature forces, and desires to fight on the side of freedom as 
an alternative to the left. Berlusconi sent a video recording 
to public and private sector news bulletins. Here is the 
passage concerning his candidacy: 
  [Begin Berlusconi recording] I have decided to enter the 
fray 
and to concern myself with public affairs because I do not want 
to live in a country which is not liberal and is governed by 
immature forces and by men tied twice over to past political and 
economic failure. In order to live the new life I have chosen, 
today I tendered my resignation from all company positions in 
the group that I founded. I am therefore giving up my role as 
editor and businessman to put my experience and all my efforts 
at the disposal of a battle in which I believe with the utmost 
conviction and with the utmost strength. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

