<H3> <TI>   Clark Comments on Denktas' Reply, Leaves for Athens </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2601173894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1500 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2601173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a statement this afternoon before leaving for 
Athens, Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special 
representative in Cyprus, said Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf 
Denktas did not give the United Nations a satisfactory answer on 
whether he accepts the confidence-building measures in 
principle. However, he appeared optimistic, saying that in his 
opinion, the negotiations are very close to reaching an 
agreement. Clark said: There is only one very significant step 
left. 

</TEXT>

