<H3> <TI>   Austrian Chancellor Visits on EU Accession Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2601160594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1230 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2601160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Austrian Chancellor Franz Vranitzky this morning 
began an official visit to Athens. Soon after arriving, the 
Austrian chancellor had a 30-minute meeting with Prime Minister 
Andreas Papandreou. Papandreou said afterward that their talks 
covered issues relating to Austria's accession to the European 
Union. We are committed, the Greek prime minister and president 
of the European Union said, to achieving the interstate 
agreements for the accession of European Free Trade Association 
countries by March. 
  The Austrian chancellor referred to his friendship with 
Papandreou and announced that a group of specialists has 
undertaken to give a new push to the negotiating package on 
issues of regional, agriculture, and land transit and transport 
policy. Asked what stance his country will take on the issue of 
Cyprus' accession to the European Union, the Austrian chancellor 
said it will be positive. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

