<F P=101> Sweden </F>
<H3> <TI>   Board To Halt Fuel Processing Cooperation With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601122494 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1100 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Swedish Nuclear Power Inspection Board will stop 
cooperation with Russia in the supervision of the processing of 
Russian nuclear fuel. According to to the Nuclear Power 
Inspection Board, the situation in Russia is so unstable that 
there is no longer any sense in cooperating. Russia is no 
longer able to fully supervise its nuclear fuel, said director 
Paul Ek from the Nuclear Power Inspection Board. 

</TEXT>

