<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Papoulias Meets Clark, Feissel, Discusses Procedure </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2701100294 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 2200 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2701100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After meeting Joe Clark and Gustave Feissel, the UN 
secretary general's special representatives in Cyprus, Foreign 
Minister Karolos Papoulias said he hopes the outcome of the 
procedure on the Cyprus issue will be positive. He added that 
efforts are being made within the framework of UN Secretary 
General Butrus Butrus-Ghali's ideas. 
  Clark described the Greek Government's public support as 
significant and helpful to the UN secretary general's offices. 
He added that to achieve progress he will need the assistance 
of the Turkish Government and the two sides in Cyprus. He and 
Feissel will go to Ankara tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-59180 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu019_a_94001" </HT>


