<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greens Protest Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701145594 Vienna DER STANDARD in German 27 Jan 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DER STANDARD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [APA report: "Protest Against China's Qiao Shi"] </F>
  [Text] Vienna -- The foreign policy spokeswoman for the 
Greens, Marijana Grandits, has "sharply protested" against 
Chancellor Vranitzky's and parliamentary president Heinz 
Fischer's reception of Chinese parliamentary president Qiao Shi. 
"As head of the police and the secret services, Qiao Shi is one 
of the most sinister figures and responsible for all human 
rights violations in China in the past few years," she stressed. 

</TEXT>

