<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   France Calls For Expanding Sanctions Against Haiti </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2701130894 Paris LE FIGARO in French 27 Jan 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> BR2701130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE FIGARO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "France In Favor of a General </F>
Embargo"] 
  [Text] On Tuesday evening [25 January] at UN Headquarters, 
France circulated a draft resolution calling for a strengthening 
of sanctions against the Haitian military junta by means of a 
general embargo on the island. The text, which still can be 
amended, recommends extending the oil and military embargo to 
all fields of activity, except humanitarian aid. The embargo 
should also apply to all noncommercial flights from or to Haiti; 
this actually applies to small aircraft involved in all kinds of 
trafficking -- mainly drug -- linked with Haiti. France 
suggests that these measures be enforced on 31 January at 11:59 
[time zone not specified]. 

</TEXT>

