<H3> <TI>   Metallurgical Trade Union Announces Warning Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601144994 Hamburg DPA in German 1247 GMT 26 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2601144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (DPA) -- The IG Metall metalworkers trade 
union has announced that warning strikes will begin in the west 
German metallurgical and electrical industry on Monday [31 
January]. The announcement was intended to get the stalled wage 
negotiations moving again, deputy chairman Walter Riester told 
journalists in Bonn today. He accused employers of "sabotaging" 
the pay talks. The assumption is not unjustified that some 
employers want to start a large-scale dispute all over the 
republic. 
  The legal moratorium on industrial action in the west German 
metal and electrical industry ends on Friday. 

</TEXT>

