<H3> <TI>   Andreatta Meets Saudi Foreign Affairs Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2601113094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 2152 GMT 25 
Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2601113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Andreatta Meets Mahmun al-Qurdi"] </F>
  [Text] Rome, 25 Jan (ANSA) -- Foreign Minister Beniamino 
Andreatta today received the Saudi Foreign Affairs under 
secretary Mahmun al-Qurdi, who is in Rome to take part in a 
meeting of the joint Italo-Saudi Commission. 
  The commission's previous meeting (the fourth in the series) 
took place in Riyadh from January 30 to February 1 of last year. 
The two men today first reviewed economic matters of common 
interest. Andreatta and al-Qurdi agreed on the advisability of 
stepping up initiatives aimed a bolstering trade and industrial 
cooperation between the two countries. 
  Recalling the Italian government privatization plan outlined 
to the Saudis when Treasury Minister Piero Barucci travelled to 
Saudi Arabia in January of 1993, Andreatta plumped for Saudi 
investments in share companies being formed from the former 
public ones. 
  The two men also discussed international matters and 
especially the situation in the Mediterranean and in Bosnia. 
The previous political contact between the two countries took 
place in November of last year when Saudi Foreign Minister Sa'ud 
al-Faysal al Sa'ud came to Rome, the Farnesina [Foreign 
Ministry] noted. 

</TEXT>

