Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Segni And Martinazzoli Reach `Full </F>
Accord'"] 
  [Text] Rome, 27 Jan (ANSA) -- People's Party [Italian 
Popular Party--PPI] Secretary Mino Martinazzoli voiced "full 
accord" with the aims of the Pact for Italy of reformer Mario 
Segni in a meeting here Thursday [27 January] morning, Segni 
aide Giuseppe Bicocchi said. 
Segni's call for direct election of a premier has long been a 
sticking point with the People's Party and its predecessor, the 
Christian Democratic Party. 
  The announcement comes just days after Segni signed a 
programme deal with the federalist Northern League, a deal which 
broke down last night when League chief Umberto Bossi said he 
would have nothing to do with the People's Party. 
  Segni is continuing a round of meetings with representatives 
from the Liberal, Socialist and other lay parties, aides said. 

