<H3> <TI>   Bonn To Form Joint Corps With Netherlands </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701183894 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1702 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701183894 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Munster (DDP/ADN) -- Following the example of the 
French-German armed forces, a joint corps will now be set up 
with the Netherlands. Federal Defense Minister Volker Ruehe and 
his Dutch counterpart, Relus ter Beek, reached agreement on 
further details in Munster today. A joint corps staff is to be 
established from October and the multinational corps is to be 
operational from 1995. A Dutch officer is to be the first 
commanding general. The official language is English, and 
German and Dutch are to be treaty languages. 

</TEXT>

